verbose_text: Furthermore, mice selectively deficient in epidermal Skint1 expression show only a minor delay in wound healing compared to mice deficient in Skint3 or Skint9, suggesting that Skint1 is mainly involved in the maturation of DETC progenitors in the thymus, and that Skint3 and Skint9 play a more important role in mediating DETC activation in the epidermis.
